# Add Secret Group

## Arguments
- `name`: Secret group name (kebab-case, e.g., `payment-api-keys`)
- `service`: Service that needs these secrets
- `keys`: Comma-separated secret key names

## Steps

### 1. Create Cloud Secrets
{{ if eq .Project.Spec.Cloud.Provider "gcp" }}- Create secrets in GCP Secret Manager:
```bash
for key in {keys}; do
  gcloud secrets create {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-{name}-$key --replication-policy=automatic
  echo -n "placeholder" | gcloud secrets versions add {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-{name}-$key --data-file=-
done
```{{ end }}{{ if eq .Project.Spec.Cloud.Provider "aws" }}- Create secrets in AWS Secrets Manager:
```bash
aws secretsmanager create-secret --name {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/{name} --secret-string '{"key":"placeholder"}'
```{{ end }}

### 2. Create ExternalSecret CR
- Create `k8s/helm/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/infra/external-secrets/templates/{name}-secret.yaml`:
```yaml
apiVersion: external-secrets.io/v1beta1
kind: ExternalSecret
metadata:
  name: {name}
  namespace: {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}
spec:
  refreshInterval: 1h
  secretStoreRef:
    name: {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-cluster-store
    kind: ClusterSecretStore
  target:
    name: {name}
    creationPolicy: Owner
  data:
    {{"{{"}} range .keys {{"}}"}}
    - secretKey: {key}
      remoteRef:
{{ if eq .Project.Spec.Cloud.Provider "gcp" }}        key: {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-{name}-{key}
        version: latest{{ end }}{{ if eq .Project.Spec.Cloud.Provider "aws" }}        key: {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/{name}
        property: {key}{{ end }}
    {{"{{"}} end {{"}}"}}
```

### 3. Reference in Service Helm Values
- Add to `k8s/helm/{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}/{group}/{service}/values.yaml`:
```yaml
secrets:
  - {name}
envFrom:
  - secretRef:
      name: {name}
```

### 4. Add Config Entries
- Add environment variables to `apps/{service}/src/config.ts` for each secret key
- Use required validation — service should fail to start if secrets are missing

### 5. Verify
- `kubectl get externalsecret {name} -n {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}` — status should be "SecretSynced"
- `kubectl get secret {name} -n {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}` — k8s secret should exist

## Critical Rules
1. Never commit actual secret values — only references
2. Always set `refreshInterval` — secrets rotate
3. Use `creationPolicy: Owner` so ESO manages the k8s Secret lifecycle
4. For local dev, create matching k8s Secrets manually or via init script

## Checklist
- [ ] Cloud secrets created with placeholder values
- [ ] ExternalSecret CR created
- [ ] Service Helm values reference the secret
- [ ] Service config validates secret presence on startup
- [ ] ExternalSecret syncs successfully
